5000|$|Drivers {{compete in}} two-driver, <b>two-sled</b> teams {{for their safety}} since they travel through remote areas of Alaska. Teams are {{required}} to take three six-hour breaks between Nome and Tanana. They also take a 42-hour break in Nome to recuperate before they start making their return. Sleds are impounded during the break, ensuring that they rest since they are not able to work on their sleds. [...] the race had never had a fatality, although there had been close calls.|$|E

